141 - Linked List Cycle
Problem Statement

Given the head of a linked list, determine whether the linked list contains a cycle.

A cycle exists if a node can be reached again by continuously following the next pointer.

Approach: Floyd's Cycle Detection Algorithm (Tortoise and Hare)
Intuition

Use two pointers:

Slow Pointer → moves one step at a time.
Fast Pointer → moves two steps at a time.

If the linked list contains a cycle, the fast pointer will eventually catch up to the slow pointer inside the cycle.

If there is no cycle, the fast pointer will reach null.

Algorithm

Initialize:

ListNode slow = head;
ListNode fast = head;

Traverse while:

fast != null && fast.next != null

Move pointers:

slow = slow.next;
fast = fast.next.next;

If:

slow == fast

return true.

If the loop ends, return false.
Code
class Solution {
    public boolean hasCycle(ListNode head) {

        ListNode slow = head;
        ListNode fast = head;

        while (fast != null && fast.next != null) {

            slow = slow.next;
            fast = fast.next.next;

            if (slow == fast) {
                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}
