Why This Works

Inside a cycle:

Slow pointer speed = 1 node/step
Fast pointer speed = 2 nodes/step

The distance between them decreases by 1 node every iteration.

Eventually, the fast pointer catches the slow pointer, proving that a cycle exists.

If no cycle exists, the fast pointer reaches the end (null).

